race.comment: DUO PERNA (2) settled towards the tail then wound up strongly to finish third when resuming last start at Murray Bridge. Will get back again from his wide gate but a repeat of the latest effort will see him in the finish again. ROYAL TRAPEZE (4) finished a close fifth last time out over 1100m at Clare nine days ago, following up on his flashing light effort first-up. Steps up in distance should measure right up. TERRITORIAN (3) has warmed nicely late in his two runs back, despite not threatening. Strips fitter third-up and will appreciate the added trip. Expect him to play a more significant role this time. ANAHORISH (11) has found tough races in her last two, after breaking the maiden in fine style to kick off the prep. Freshened with 36 days and strikes a much more suitable assignment with Opperman reuniting. Can give this a big shake with a return to form. CUBAN WATERS (8) found it a bit too tough in town last time but was a winner in this grade two back. Don't underestimate.
